{"author":{"id":"144ad87499f23e542ca19f06c7fd2eff0a1056f0f72b792d2cb236eca4d75d06"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1533436426,"nonce":"NkUVuh+5mSN8C+Pxy+JUTSiF8dc=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUzNDc2NjMzODE=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/2021","origin":"github"},"title":"MultiQC v1.6 now available","message":"I was running MultiQC today in usegalaxy.eu and the datasets had a warning in the history that a new version was available, see below. \n\nWould be great to have 1.6 as it has a module for fastp and there's already a [Bioconda package](https://anaconda.org/bioconda/multiqc) (nice!) \n\n\u003cimg width=\"966\" alt=\"screen shot 2018-08-05 at 12 26 00 pm\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5591821/43682062-2652ee24-98ab-11e8-8e1a-3e6f54c36e5f.png\"\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\nBtw this version was only released 1 day ago and that automated notification about a new version being available is pretty cool imo. Was wondering if something like that could be used to do the automated notifications that @Slugger70 raised at the GCC IUC meeting? And/or if that warning about a new version available could be captured and turned into an email notification or automated issue creation in the IUC repo?","files":null}]}